widgets_values:
# I

### (Down-)Load Models and place here
Use your favorit checkpoints, LoRas, ... **A LIST OF ALL THE USED MODELS CAN BE FOUND IN THE README.md file in the Repo/Zip**
people, human, face, hand, feet, shoe, leg, bag, backpack, pet, dog, cat, gun, animal

# V

### Processes and ADVANCED configuration
All the magic happens here. Some Nodes have been collapsed to save space. ***Do not mess with this* until you know what you are doing.**

# II

### Image Inputs
Put your inputs/renderings/renderelements for creating from preprocessors and/or using canny/depth/... map direct. **BASE IMAGE is MANDATORY**, every other input is optional

# IV

### Preprocessors & Masks
If needed/For testing plug different Controllers & Masks to your Setup at the bottom of this section (e.g. try a different Canny Preprocessor in Apply Controlnet). **ONLY THE CONNECTED PREPROCESSERS ARE MANDATORY** (Image Edge Detection & DepthAnythingV2 nodes at the bottom).

# III

### BASIC Configuration
Bypass Groups that you dont need for faster Generations (e.g. everything with PPL if you dont want people to be added/detailed).
Set Switches and Sliders according to your **INPUT IMAGES in *Section II.*** By default ***GENERATION*** mode is set to 1 (meaning the workflow creates a new image from canny/depth). Providing a basic 3d Rendering in ***BASE IMAGE*** and setting GENERATION to 2 will enhance/change your rendering by the PERCENTAGE value provided in ***DENOISE*** (e.g. 0.05 = 5 %).
